                            <comment id="12901516" author="thiruvel" created="Mon, 23 Aug 2010 18:06:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Same is the case with CLASSPATH, its being reset.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;CLASSPATH=&quot;${HIVE_CONF_DIR}&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12901524" author="thiruvel" created="Mon, 23 Aug 2010 18:27:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching patch.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What users set on the shell for CLASSPATH or HADOOP_CLASSPATH will be picked up first. I guess thats OK.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12901766" author="amareshwari" created="Tue, 24 Aug 2010 08:14:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch looks fine to me.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12902149" author="jsensarma" created="Tue, 24 Aug 2010 23:20:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 on HADOOP_CLASSPATH.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;i am not sure about CLASSPATH. Hadoop itself does not allow users to supply pre-existing value for CLASSPATH. here&apos;s snippet from 0.20 conf:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;CLASSPATH initially contains $HADOOP_CONF_DIR&lt;br/&gt;
CLASSPATH=&quot;${HADOOP_CONF_DIR}&quot;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

</comment>
